Privacy Policy
Blake Crosley edited this pageÂ on Jul 10, 2024

941 Apps, LLC ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is collected, used, and disclosed by our app, Ace Citizenship.

**Information We Collect**

Ace Citizenship collects minimal user data to provide and improve our service:

1. User-Entered Information: We store your selected state and representative name locally on your device to personalize your experience.

2. App Preferences: We store your app settings (such as light/dark mode preferences, haptics, and audio feedback settings) locally on your device.

**How We Use Your Information**

The information we collect is used solely to provide and improve the Ace Citizenship app experience. We do not share, sell, or disclose your information to third parties.

**Data Storage and Security**

All data collected by Ace Citizenship is stored locally on your device. We do not transfer or store your data on external servers.

**Children's Privacy**

Ace Citizenship is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

**Changes to This Privacy Policy**

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.

**Contact Us**

If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, please get in touch with us at blake@941apps.com.

By using Ace Citizenship, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
